Class CounterSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<Counter<?>>
        • org.apache.beam.sdk.util.common.CounterSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Counter<?>>, Collection<Counter<?>>, Set<Counter<?>>

    public class CounterSet
extends AbstractSet<Counter<?>>
    A CounterSet maintains a set of Counters.

    Thread-safe.

      • addOrReuseCounter

        public <T> Counter<T> addOrReuseCounter(Counter<T> counter)
        Adds the given Counter to this CounterSet.

        If a counter with the same name already exists, it will be reused, as long as it is compatible.

        Returns:
        the Counter that was reused, or added
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a counter with the same name but an incompatible kind had already been added

      • addCounter

        public boolean addCounter(Counter<?> counter)
        Adds a counter. Returns true if the counter was added to the set and false if the given counter was null or it already existed in the set.
        Parameters:
